</ul>
<b>What to eat?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Diet plays a very important role in treating acne. More so, because this ailment is a reflection of various other problems that may be a part of your body already. An unclean stomach for example, could cause pimples while dandruff could cause acne on the forehead etc. Eating right, prima facie, is a treatment for acne. Hereâ€™s your guide to eat right:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Gorge on Omega-3 fatty acids: Anti- inflammatory foods can help your skin in many ways. You must have walnuts, almonds, flax seeds, Kale and mustard seeds too.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Dairy products: Consuming dairy products help in calming your stomach and in turn, help in providing you with a clear skin.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Green tea: Green tea helps in detoxification of the body.Â Â </span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Balanced diet: Eat foods of all shapes and colours. Have a variety of fruits and vegetables as a routine.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Have plenty of water.</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Treatments</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A dermatologist will help you in getting treated for acne. Chemical peels, medications and therapies could come in handy to treat this. More often, a healthy diet and physical exercise along with proper hydration can do wonders.</span>

