<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Increase in Heartbeat</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chest pain</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Slow heartbeat</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shortness of breath</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dizziness</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Keeping your heart health</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">People with arrhythmia need to keep their heart healthy. And hereâ€™s the best way to do this:</span>

<b>Limit your caffeine intake: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">People who love coffee or energy drinks should, at least stay conscious of how much they drink. For energy drinks, its best to strictly avoid them.</span>

<b>Reduce alcohol intake: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Alcohol is known to increase blood pressure which has been linked to Heart Arrhythmias.</span>

<b>Stay active: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exercise improves heart health. It's advisable to choose cardio over weightlifting exercises. As opposed to peopleâ€™s notion, yoga helps to improve the symptoms of Heart Arrhythmias.</span>

<b>Shed off some pounds: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the most significant steps to take is to shed off some extra weight. Overweight or obese people are at higher risk of having Heart arrhythmias or even other heart related problems. Warning: don't try to lose weight with diet pills; it can cause Heart Arrhythmias.</span>

<b>Sleep well for a healthy heart: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sleeping very well prevents the risk of developing the condition. It helps to reduce the stress pressure in the heart. Sleeping period of 7-9 hours in a day is healthy enough.</span>

<b>Don't be nonchalant with your Heart arrhythmias: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">While your doctor might tell you that your Heart arrhythmias may not mean any harm, that doesnâ€™t mean it cannot lead to serious cases. It can lead to uncomfortable conditions that you may not be able to live with. Always keep them in check.</span>

<b>Avoid smoking: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stay clear of smoking. It can cause heart diseases including Heart Arrhythmias.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Obviously, you can live a healthy life with arrhythmias. Always maintain your heart health.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œillness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus: </span><b>Longstanding emotional problems. Lack of joy. Hardening of the heart. Belief in strain and stress.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing Heart arrhythmia is: </span><b>My heart beats to the rhythm of love</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:26;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1155";s:4:"name";s:9:"Arthritis";s:4:"slug";s:9:"arthritis";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1155";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:3604:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Arthritis stays around us, yet its effect on people, their families, employers and the world at large is far beyond the imagination. Globally, Arthritis is a form of joint disease and is the leading cause of disabilities among Older Adults. Newborn and children are not left out. In fact, annually, over 300,000 newborn and children in the world have it. In 2019, the number of people expected to have arthritis is estimated to be around 78 million. There are two types of Arthritis: Rheumatoid Arthritis and Osteoarthritis.Â </span>

<b>Rheumatoid Arthritis</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Rheumatoid arthritis is a chronic inflammatory disorder which can affect more than the joints. In fact, for some, this condition can result in the damage of other parts of the body system, including the eyes, skin, lungs, and blood vessels.</span>

<b>SymptomsÂ </b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">They include:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Warm, tender, swollen joints</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">The stiffness of the joints- generally worse early in the morning or after a long time of idleness</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fever, fatigue, and appetite loss</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Risk factors</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Factors that may increase the chances of rheumatoid arthritis include age, sex, smoking, and family history.</span>

<b>Osteoarthritis</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Osteoarthritis is the most prevalent type of arthritis that affects millions of people from all over the world. This form of arthritis occurs when the protective cartilage at the edges of the bone wears out.</span><b>Â </b>

<b>Symptoms</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Symptoms of Osteoarthritis typically develop slowly and become worse over time. They include:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stiffness</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tenderness</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Lifestyle changes to tackle Arthritis</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Eat a healthy diet that contains antioxidants to prevent inflammation</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Maintain an exercise regimen to keep the joints flexible</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Also make sure youâ€™re not overweight as that tends to put more pressure on the knee joints</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow good sleeping habits so you get adequate, good quality rest.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Meditation can help one calm down and also visualise healing.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Traditional western methods are widely used for treating Arthritis, Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to Louise Hay, the main cause of Arthritis is:</span><b> Criticism, feeling unloved, bitterness, and resentment.Â </b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing Arthritis is: </span><b>I am love. I choose to love and approve of myself. I see others with love</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:27;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1172";s:4:"name";s:6:"Asthma";s:4:"slug";s:6:"asthma";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1172";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4214:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Have you ever noticed how some people in the locality have breathing problems at Diwali time especially when crackers are being burst nearby? Or say, the â€˜puff or asthalinâ€™ a lot of children carry to school? These are children or people who have breathing problems as a result of asthma. Around the globe, roughly 2,50,000 die of asthma every year.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Asthma is a condition of the bronchial tubes or the airways to the lungs. The ailment causes inflammation or swelling in the bronchial tubes and can make you breathless. Asthma is pretty common and those with asthma do not ever get fully cured, but the disease can be managed very well now. Extremely emotional events could also lead to asthma attacks.</span>

<b>Types</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There are many types of asthma, depending on their onset and severity. Some of them are:</span>

<b>Childhood asthma</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: This is an intermittent form of asthma and reportedly, more children experience asthma attacks than elders. Second-hand smoke, cigarette exposure could be reasons for developing childhood asthma.</span>

<b>Adult-onset asthma</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: Asthma can begin at any age. Adult-onset asthma could be a result of other ailments too. For example, obesity is a major risk factor.</span>

<b>Occupational asthma</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: This is a kind of asthma that occurs as a result of any profession or occupation.</span>

<b>Seasonal asthma</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: This is one of the most commonly heard-of. For some people, the environment around them and even the climate can trigger asthma. For example, the weather, Diwali time because of the smoke caused by crackers, and so on.</span>

<b>Causes</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Genetics</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Allergies</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Smoking/ exposure to smoking</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Environmental factors like pollution</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Obesity</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Smoking during pregnancy</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Stress</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Menstrual cycle</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Symptoms</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Shortness of breath</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Chest tightness</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Chest pain</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Wheezing</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Cough</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Lack of sleep due to breathlessness</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Treatments</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Asthma, like we said earlier cannot be fully cured. However, asthma can be managed pretty well. Its symptoms can be kept under control. Medications like combination inhalers or anti-inflammatory drugs could come in handy for you. Immunotherapy has also proven to be useful in case of some kinds of asthma.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done path breaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of asthma is: </span><b>Smothering love. Inability to breathe for one's self. Feeling stifled. Suppressed crying.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One way of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations. Doing this regularly can help to reduce the debilitating effects of this illness.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for treating asthma is</span><b>: It is safe now for me to take charge of my own life. I choose to be free.</b>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:32;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1284";s:4:"name";s:9:"Back Pain";s:4:"slug";s:9:"back-pain";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1284";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:5328:"<strong>Back Pain</strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sitting is the new smoking. Sedentary lifestyles have become the norm with most interactions taking place in the virtual world. All this downward facing into the smartphone can result in a bad posture. Ergo, back pain. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Though trauma and fractures can cause back pain, the more common reason is an everyday activity performed incorrectly: carrying a heavy laptop bag on the shoulder instead of in a backpack, bending over to pick up something from the floor, slouched over on the couch binge-watching Netflix.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The situation in India is quite dismal. According to a </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">World Spine Day 2017 Insights Report by a well-known Spine Clinic, 41.2% of the population in India suffers from Herniated Disc (Slipped Disc) and the most common pain is lower back pain.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Back pain can range from mild to completely disabling. It is cited as one of the top reasons for staying at home from work but gentle exercise works better than bed rest for healing it as can balms and lotions.</span>

<b>Symptoms of back pain</b>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stiff back</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain in the lower back that radiates down the back of the leg</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain that erupts only on movement</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Intermittent pain</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Preventing Back Pain</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The spinal column, our backbone, holds the weight of the head and the torso. Its flexibility allows us to twist and turn in any direction and perform many acrobatic actions. Taking care of this precious asset will keep our back happy and consequently, us too.</span>

<b>Here are some effective tips:</b>
<ol>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Become stress-free: Stress causes us to tense our muscles and this can cause a backache.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exercise: Our body is made for movement. Exercise keeps the joints flexible and this can</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Good posture: Invest in ergonomic furniture and make sure you take a short walking break every hour at work so your muscles remain flexible and the back remains strong.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sleep sideways: The back gets proper support when one sleeps sideways . Avoid sleeping on the back or stomach but if you must, support your neck and lower back with rolled towels or small pillows.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Healthy diet: Keep your digestive system working well with the right balance and mix of foods. This will avoid putting a strain on your back.</span></li>
</ol>
<b>Going beyond the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œ</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Illness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€ </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the back represents the support of life. Each kind of back problem arises on account of a corresponding emotional state and one way of healing them are through saying or writing affirmations. Given below are some of the underlying causes of back conditions and the affirmations to heal them:</span>

<b>Rounded shoulders:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Carrying the burdens of life. Feeling helpless and hopeless.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Lower back pain: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fear of money or lack of financial support. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Affirmation: I trust the process of life. All I need is taken care of. I am safe. Â </b><b>
</b><b>
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Mid-Back Pain: Guilt. Stuck in all that stuff back there. â€œGet off my back!â€ </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Affirmation: I release the past. I am free to move forward with love in my heart.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Upper Back Pain: Lack of emotional support. Feeling unloved. Holding back love. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">
</span><b>Affirmation: I love and approve of myself. Life supports and loves me.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Back Curvature: The inability to flow with the support of life. Fear and trying to hold on to old ideas. Not trusting life. Lack of integrity. No courage of conviction</span>

<b>Other alternative therapies that have also given good results for treating this back pain are: </b><b>
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Reiki, Hypnotherapy,Access Bar, Acupressure, Hatha Yoga, Vinyasa Yoga, Ashtanga Yoga, Reflexology, Iyengar Yoga, Cranio Sacral Therapy</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"4";}i:36;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1345";s:4:"name";s:12:"Birth Trauma";s:4:"slug";s:12:"birth-trauma";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1345";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:38;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1379";s:4:"name";s:11:"Black Magic";s:4:"slug";s:11:"black-magic";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1379";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:39;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1197";s:4:"name";s:14:"Bladder Cancer";s:4:"slug";s:14:"bladder-cancer";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1197";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"2";}i:41;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1134";s:4:"name";s:25:"Bradycardia (Arrhythmia )";s:4:"slug";s:22:"bradycardia-arrhythmia";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1134";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4207:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">A normal heartbeat starts from 60 to 100 beats per minute. Anything slower than the minimum of 60 beats per minutes is abnormal. This abnormal condition is called Bradycardia.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to World Health Organization, â€œApproximately 3% of the world population suffers from Bradycardia.â€</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Â Bradycardia can result in serious complications if the heart fails to pump blood with enough oxygen to the body. For some people, bradycardia poses no complications.</span>

<b>However, a typical condition of Bradycardia can cause:</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fainting</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fatigue</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dizziness</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shortness of breath</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Short memory</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chest pain</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Maintaining Your Heart Health - An Effective Way To Treating Bradycardia</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Include the following activities into your daily routine to improve your heart health and fight Bradycardia:</span>

<b>Regularly exercise and eat healthily</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Maintain a daily exercise and eat foods high in fat with less salt and sugar. Fruits and vegetables are also a good option. Foods rich in omega 3 reduce bad cholesterol and increase good cholesterol. The following foods contain omega 3 which you can add to your diet:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Walnuts</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Herring</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sardine</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Natto (Japanese fermented soybeans)</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hemp seeds</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chia seeds</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Egg yolks</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Add L-Carnitine into your diet</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Always take up to 2,000mg of L-carnitine every day. You can get it from whole milk.</span>

<b>Keep Your Weight Under Control</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Being overweight triggers your risk of having a heart disease.</span>

<b>Maintain a normal blood pressure and cholesterol level</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Improve your lifestyle habits and take steps to prevent high blood pressure.</span>

<b>Quit smoking</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Stop smoking and if you find it hard to do, seek a professional help.Â </span>

<b>Reduce stress</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Getting busy always, everyday stressor and not finding the time to rest can lead to stress.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Although you may need to do some trial and error, look for the stress reliever that'll work for you.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Yoga is a good way to induce a sense wellbeing and calmness. Express your fears and feelings by writing them in a journal. Listening to music that makes you happy is also a good way to stay calm. Meditation is the ultimate de-stresser. Spending a few minutes meditating as soon as you wake up or while going to sleep will pay dividends.</span>

<b>Going beyond the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of Bradycardia is:</span><b> Longstanding emotional problems. Lack of joy. Hardening of the heart. Belief in strain and stress.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of doing this is through saying or writing affirmations. Her affirmation for healingÂ BradycardiaÂ  is â€œ</span><b><i>My heart beats to the rhythm of love</i></b><span style="font-weight: 400;">â€.</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:42;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1364";s:4:"name";s:8:"Break up";s:4:"slug";s:8:"break-up";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1364";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:2520:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">A relationship breakup, usually referred to as a breakup, occurs when the two parties involved decide to terminate their intimate relationship. In slang, this act is popularly called, â€œdumping someoneâ€ when the process is initiated by one of the involved party.</span>

<b>Why Do People Break Up?</b>

<b>Cheating</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Cheating or infidelity is the leading cause of most breakups. Men and women cheat for reasons best known to them.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Most cases of cheating started with a seemingly innocent friendship. Itâ€™s really hard to rebuild a relationship after cheating.</span>

<b>Financial infidelity</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Money controls everything. Everything ranging from expenses to financial goals to spending habits causing everyday complaints can end a relationship. Financial infidelity is one of the highest causes of divorce, after infidelity.</span>

<b>Lack of communication</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Communication defines a healthy relationship. The inability to communicate effectively can destroy a beautiful affair.</span>

<b>Being unsupportive</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If partners cannot support each other when down or stressed by some life events, then the relationship isnâ€™t worth it and itâ€™s heading to the rocks soon.</span>

<b>How To Avoid A BreakupÂ </b>

<b>Remove the thoughts of breaking up</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The idea that youâ€™ll be a better person without your partner can destroy your motivation to make the relationship work. Keeping in mind that breaking up is a â€œNO, NOâ€ can strengthen the bond in your relationship.</span>

<b>Always respect your partner</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your partner is the best and thatâ€™s why you fell in love with them in the first place. The best way you prove it is by showing them some respect.</span>

<b>Improve your communication</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Nothing can substitute those regular talks and gossips between lovers. When there is sharing of thoughts and feelings, the bond between partners grows stronger. Partners should set aside some time every day to just discuss together.</span>

<b>Be supportive</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Do your best to give your partner what they need most. Even if they donâ€™t open up on their needs, find a way to figure it out. And if youâ€™re unsure, just ask!</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"4";}i:43;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1190";s:4:"name";s:13:"Breast Cancer";s:4:"slug";s:13:"breast-cancer";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1190";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4324:"Breast cancer constitutes to over 16% of cancers in women all over the world. In fact, in 2019, 1 out of every 8 women risk diagnose of breast cancer in their lifetime. It is the second big cause of cancer death among women (after cancer of the lungs). This uncontrollable growth usually develops into a tumor which is felt like a bump and visible only on an x-ray. According to Lucy Stenon, a breast cancer specialist from the University of York, â€œAlertness of the symptoms and necessity of screening are imperative ways of lowering the riskâ€. In breast cancer, ÑĞµlls Ñ–n brĞµĞ°st tÑ–ssuĞµ ÑhĞ°ngĞµ (Ğ¾r mutĞ°tĞµ) Ğ°nd kĞµĞµÑ€ rĞµÑ€rĞ¾duÑÑ–ng. Ğ¢hĞµsĞµ Ğ°bnĞ¾rmĞ°l ÑĞµlls usuĞ°llÑƒ ÑlustĞµr tĞ¾gĞµthĞµr tĞ¾ fĞ¾rm Ğ° tumĞ¾r. There are several factors that constitutes to the increased chances of developing breast cancer. They include menopausal hormone use, life expectancy, changes in reproductive process, and lots more.

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Quick diagnosis of breast cancer improves the chances of recovery.</span>

<b>Symptoms of Breast Cancer</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Symptoms of breast cancer are generally noticed in areas of the breast with thickened tissues or a lump in the breast or armpit region.</span>

<b>Some other symptoms are:</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Pains in the breast or armpits</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Redness or pitting of the breast skin</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Rashes around or one some parts of the nipples</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Nipple discharge that sometimes contains blood</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Inverted or sunken nipples</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">A sudden change in breast shape or size</span></li>
</ul>
<b>What causes Breast Cancer?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">When a woman reaches puberty, her breast contains fats, connective tissues, and several glands that manufacture milk for breastfeeding. Ducts or Tiny tubes take the milk to the nipple. Â Often, breast cancer starts in the interior lining of the lobules or milk ducts that provide milk.</span>

<b>Prevention</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There is no specific way to prevent breast cancer, although certain lifestyle preferences can exceptionally lower the chances of breast cancer. They are:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Steering clear of excessive alcohol intake</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Routinely pursuing a healthy diet containing fruits and vegetables</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Regular exercise</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Maintaining a good Body Mass Index</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Women should carefully examine their breastfeeding options and avoid using HRT after menopause because these can increase the risk.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Traditional western methods are widely used for treating Breast cancer, Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œillness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of Breast cancer is: </span><b>Feeling unloved, and failure to nourish oneself. </b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing Breast Cancer is: </span><b>I embrace and trust life knowing that I am safe and loved. I choose to love and be loved</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"2";}i:47;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1189";s:4:"name";s:6:"Cancer";s:4:"slug";s:6:"cancer";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1189";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4984:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Cancer affects everyone - the rich and poor, the young and old, men and women, including children.Â  Cancer is one of the highest causes of mortality rate in the world. Yet, it is possible to avoid many of these deaths. 30-50% of cancers can be prevented by healthy lifestyles like avoiding tobacco and immunizing against infections that may cause cancer.</span>

