<span style="font-weight: 400;">Intimate partner abuse is the leading cause of public health problems, globally affecting over 2 million women and 800,000 men. It is the major cause of injury, homelessness and death including murder.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The statistics of those affected by domestic violence from across the world is worrisome: domestic violence occurs in over 20% of current adult relationships, with women being a victim.</span>

<b>How does it affect health?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Domestic violence has a significant effect and consequences on health. It could lead to anxiety, depression, and other abuse disorder. Violent abuse of pregnant women can lead to the delivery of babies with low-birth-weight. Children of victim can suffer a declined intellectual functioning.</span>

