-Â <span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"2";}i:140;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1125";s:4:"name";s:36:"High Blood Pressure ( Hypertension )";s:4:"slug";s:32:"high-blood-pressure-hypertension";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1125";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4914:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">High blood pressure is a very common condition in which the heart works harder to pump blood into the body and may eventually cause heart problems like heart disease. Globally, high blood pressure has claimed over 7.5 million deaths. It accounts for 12.8% of the total global deaths.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Worldwide, the general prevalence of high blood pressure is in adults older than 25 years. And due to aging and population increment, the overall number of persons affected with high blood pressure-induced hypertension has risen from 600 million in 1980 to 1 billion in 2008. Itâ€™s possible to have high blood pressure for years without showing symptoms.</span>

<b>Symptoms Of High Blood Pressure</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Most cases of high blood pressure started with no symptoms, even when they reach a life-threatening level.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Only a few people with high blood pressure show generic signs like headache, nosebleeds, or shortness of breath, but these signs arenâ€™t particular to high blood pressure and may be ignored.</span>

<b>Causes Of High Blood Pressure</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">High blood pressure is made up of two types: primary hypertension and secondary hypertension.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Primary hypertension usually develops slowly for years. Secondary hypertension can be caused by hidden health conditions such as sleep apnea, thyroid problem, kidney problem, wrong medication like a birth control pill.</span>

<b>Risk Factors Of High Blood Pressure</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Some risk factors of high blood pressure include:</span>

<b>Age: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">The risk of developing high blood pressure increases with age. The disease is more prevalent in men above the age of 64 and 65 for women.</span>

<b>Family history: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">In some families, high blood pressure is hereditary.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Other risk factors include being overweight, physical inactivity, excessive alcohol intake, and smoking of tobacco.</span>

<b>Treatment Of High Blood Pressure</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Lifestyle changes can play a huge role in preventing high blood pressure. Some of the lifestyle changes include:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exercising</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Eating heart-healthy foods</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consuming less salt</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Controlling your weight</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Reducing alcohol intake</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">However, some cases may require medical attention.</span>

<b>Treating High Blood Pressure with lifestyle changes</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Lifestyle changes can play a huge role in preventing high blood pressure. Some of the lifestyle changes include:</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Weight loss is the most important step to control blood pressure. Shed off extra pounds and stay conscious of your waistline as excessive weights around your waistline can increase your chances of high blood pressure.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Often times, blood pressure increases with weight. Also, being overweight obstructs sleep, which further increases blood pressure.</span>

<b>Maintain a regular exercise</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A regular 30 minutes of exercise daily can lower your blood pressure by up to 8 mm Hg. Some types of exercises that reduce blood pressure include jogging, walking, swimming, cycling or dancing.</span>

<b>Maintain a healthy diet</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Eating a diet rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and low-fat dairy can lower your blood pressure. .</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Limit your daily alcohol intake.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of High Blood Pressure:</span><b>Longstanding emotional problem not solved.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing High Blood Pressure is: </span><b>I am alive to the joy of living. I deserve and accept the very best of life. I love and rejoice in my masculinity</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:2:"16";}i:141;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1147";s:4:"name";s:35:"High Cholesterol ( Hyperlipidemia )";s:4:"slug";s:31:"high-cholesterol-hyperlipidemia";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1147";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:222:"<b>Cause of High CholesterolÂ  </b>: Clogging the channels of joy.
<b>Affirmation:</b>Â I choose to love life. My channels of Joy are wide open. It is safe to receive.

