<b>Treatment</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Treatment for lung cancer depends heavily on 3 factors: Overall health, stage of the cancer and the location of cancer.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Chemotherapy will be your doctorâ€™s first mode of medication. Everything depends on the severity of the condition you are currently undergoing. Surgery could also be other mode of treatment. Radiation therapy is said to be quite helpful too. Of all the above, targeted radiation therapy is one of the most banked upon option.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done path breaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, â€œIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.â€</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of cancer is: </span><b>Deep hurt. Longstanding resentment. Deep secret or grief eating away at the self. Carrying hatreds. "What's the use?"</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One way of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations. Doing this regularly can help to reduce the debilitating effects of this illness. </span>

